observations.recommendation:
We recommend the following:

a. Management should create an inventory committee and direct to conduct a regular physical inventory of its Property, Plant and Equipment, pursuant to the provision of Section 156 of COA Circular No. 92-386 dated October 20, 1992;

b.  A periodic reconciliation of the PPE ledger cards maintained by the accountant with that of the Property Cards maintained by the Supply Officer should be regularly made to promptly detect any discrepancies and appropriate adjustments in both records should be out rightly recorded and reflected in the book of accounts;

c.  Management should comply strictly with the aforementioned provisions of PPSAS 17.

Recommendations:
We recommend the following:
Management should create an inventory committee and direct to conduct a regular physical inventory of its Property, Plant and Equipment, pursuant to the provision of Section 156 of COA Circular No. 92-386 dated October 20, 1992;
A periodic reconciliation of the PPE ledger cards maintained by the accountant with that of the Property Cards maintained by the Supply Officer should be regularly made to promptly detect any discrepancies and appropriate adjustments in both records should be out rightly recorded and reflected in the book of accounts;
Management should comply strictly with the aforementioned provisions of PPSAS 17.
